theorem
Th81: (for D being (u.s.c._decomposition of X) holds (for t being (Point of ( space D )) holds (for G being (a_neighborhood of ( ( Proj D ) " { t } )) holds ( ( Proj D ) .: G ) is (a_neighborhood of t))))
proof
let D being (u.s.c._decomposition of X);
let t being (Point of ( space D ));
let G being (a_neighborhood of ( ( Proj D ) " { t } ));
A1: (the carrier of ( space D )) = D by CKB44:def 1;
then ( ( Proj D ) " { t } ) = t by EQREL_1:66;
then consider W being (Subset of X) such that A2: W is  open and A3: ( ( Proj D ) " { t } ) c= W and A4: W c= G and A5: (for B being (Subset of X) holds ((B in D & B meets W) implies B c= W)) by A1,CKB59:def 1;
set Q = ( ( Proj D ) .: W );
A6: ( ( Proj D ) .: ( ( Proj D ) " { t } ) ) c= Q by A3,RELAT_1:123;
( union Q ) = ( ( proj D ) " Q ) by A1,EQREL_1:67
.= W by A5,EQREL_1:69;
then ( union Q ) in (the topology of X) by A2,PRE_TOPC:def 2;
then Q in (the topology of ( space D )) by A1,CKB46:1;
then A7: Q is  open by PRE_TOPC:def 2;
( rng ( Proj D ) ) = (the carrier of ( space D )) by CKB50:1;
then { t } c= Q by A6,FUNCT_1:77;
then A8: t in Q by ZFMISC_1:31;
Q c= ( ( Proj D ) .: G ) by A4,RELAT_1:123;
then t in ( Int ( ( Proj D ) .: G ) ) by A7,A8,TOPS_1:22;
hence thesis by CONNSP_2:def 1;
end;
